    "dynamic_rich_text_6g4djg": {
      "type": "dynamic-rich-text",
      "name": "t:sections.rich_text.presets.rich_text.name",
      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Professional-Grade Spot and Flood Lights Built for Every Vehicle and Mission</h2><p>At Strobes N’ More, we understand that dependable lighting makes all the difference in high-stakes situations. Our wide selection of <strong>auto flood lights</strong> and <strong>vehicle spot lights</strong> is trusted by police, fire departments, tow operators, construction crews, and off-road adventurers across the country.</p><p>We stock everything from high-intensity <strong>LED flood lights</strong> to ultra-focused <strong>vehicle-mounted spotlights</strong>, giving you complete control over illumination based on your mission. Whether you're lighting up a scene with a <strong>vehicle spotlight floodlight combo</strong> or directing beams with adjustable <strong>LED car spot lights</strong>, our equipment delivers unmatched performance and longevity.</p><p>All of our <strong>scenelights</strong> and <strong>automotive flood lights</strong> are tested for durability, waterproofing, and heat resistance. Need a <strong>spotlight for your car</strong> that mounts to roof racks or push bumpers? Looking for dual-beam <strong>spot/flood lights</strong> with switchable modes? We have solutions for every professional and personal use case.</p><p>Strobes N’ More stands behind our gear with expert support and fast shipping. Choose lighting that’s built to last, no matter the conditions. Browse our collection and equip your vehicle with the best <strong>emergency floodlights</strong> and <strong>spot lights for cars</strong> available today.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
    },
    "dynamic_rich_text_L8RbH8": {
      "type": "dynamic-rich-text",
      "name": "t:sections.rich_text.presets.rich_text.name",
      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Why Emergency Vehicles Need Purpose-Built LED Lighting</h2><p>EVs are built around efficiency, quiet operation, and advanced electronics. Your lighting needs to complement that, not fight it:</p><ul><li><strong>Low current draw:</strong> LED lights sip power from the 12V system, helping preserve range and reduce strain on EV electrical components.</li><li><strong>Instant, high-intensity output:</strong> LEDs reach full brightness instantly—critical for emergency braking, traffic direction, or scene lighting.</li><li><strong>Smaller, cooler housings:</strong> Compact, cool-running modules are easier to mount on sleek EV body lines and behind aerodynamic fascias.</li><li><strong>Smart control integration:</strong> Many lights in this collection support multiple flash patterns and sync capabilities, ideal for modern EV controllers and CAN-bus-friendly installs.</li></ul><p>The result is an EV that remains quiet, efficient, and safe—without sacrificing the commanding visibility that professional vehicles demand.</p><h2>LED Light Types Available for Your EV</h2><p>This collection brings together the core LED categories you need to build a complete EV lighting package:</p><h3>Hide-Away LED Strobe Lights</h3><p><a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/hide-away-leds\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Hide-away LEDs mount</span></a> inside EV headlamps, taillamps, or factory housings to create powerful, undercover flashes without adding external fixtures. They’re ideal for:</p><ul><li>Unmarked EVs or supervisor units</li><li>Clean, factory-like exterior lines</li><li>Stealth installs that still deliver serious warning power</li></ul><h3>Surface Mount LED Lights</h3><p><a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/body-grill-mount\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Surface mounts</span></a> and <a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/blogs/informative/led-headlights\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">lightheads</span></a> are the workhorses of EV lighting. They’re slim enough to fit on modern bumpers, liftgates, fascia panels, or side bodywork, yet bright enough for primary warning. Use them for:</p><ul><li>Grille, bumper, and trunk-lid installs</li><li>Perimeter and intersection warning</li><li>Compact EVs where every inch of space matters</li></ul><h3>LED Stick Lights</h3><p><a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/led-stick-lights\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Stick lights</span></a> provide linear coverage along the rear deck, hatch, or interior window line—perfect for compact EV SUVs, crossovers, and vans. They shine in:</p><ul><li>Rear warning on electric patrol SUVs</li><li>Interior window mounts in EV hatchbacks</li><li>Multi-color, directional signaling for traffic control</li></ul><h3>Dash & Window Mount LED Lights</h3><p><a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/dash-window-mount\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Dash and windshield-mounted lights</span></a> give you strong forward or rear warning without permanent exterior changes—great for leased EVs or shared fleet vehicles. They’re easy to install, reposition, or remove when vehicles rotate out of service.</p><h3>Rocker Panel LED Lights</h3><p><a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/rocker-panel-leds\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Rocker panel LEDs</span></a> tuck along the lower sides of the vehicle, creating a distinct “curtain of light” that makes EVs more visible at intersections, in parking lots, and in tight urban environments. They’re especially valuable on quiet EVs that may otherwise surprise pedestrians.</p><h3>Flood, Scene & Spot LED Lights</h3><p>EVs often serve double duty—responding to calls and working scenes. <a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/flood-scene-spotlights\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Flood, scene, and spot LEDs</span></a> help you:</p><ul><li>Light up work zones, accident scenes, or job sites</li><li>Illuminate EV cargo bays and tool areas</li><li>Provide safer, glare-controlled lighting for personnel on the ground</li></ul><h3>Accent Colors & Specialty LEDs</h3><p>Green and purple LEDs, accent lighting, and specialty colors are available for specific agencies, command vehicles, or awareness builds. They let your EV stand out while still meeting local guidelines and department standards.</p><h3>Brake, Tail, Turn & Reverse LEDs</h3><p>Upgrading to <a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/brake-tail-turn-reverse\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">LED brake, tail, and turn lighting</span></a> improves reaction times for drivers behind your EV, while bright reverse LEDs make backing safer in tight spaces, parking structures, and night operations.</p><h3>Mounting Brackets & Accessories</h3><p>Finally, mounting brackets and accessories help you adapt lights to EV-specific body styles: from unique rooflines and glass hatches to plastic bumpers and composite panels. Clean, secure mounting protects your investment and your vehicle.</p><h2>Key Features of Strobes N’ More LED Lights for EVs</h2><p>Across this collection, you’ll find professional-grade features that align perfectly with EV demands:</p><ul><li><strong>Next-generation optics:</strong> Advanced optics focus light where it’s needed most, improving real-world visibility without wasting power.</li><li><strong>High-output LEDs:</strong> Many products use high-watt diodes to deliver intense output in compact housings, ideal for tight EV mounting locations.</li><li><strong>Multiple flash patterns:</strong> Built-in patterns let you switch between response, directional, scene, and cruise modes quickly.</li><li><strong>Multi-color options:</strong> Dual- and tri-color heads support different modes and jurisdictions—<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/amber-lights\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">amber for utility</span></a>, red/blue for emergency, white for floods.</li><li><strong>Slim, low-profile housings:</strong> Designed to match modern vehicle styling, maintaining EV aerodynamics and aesthetics.</li><li><strong>Durable, weather-sealed construction:</strong> Sealed housings and robust materials handle rain, snow, road grime, and car-wash duty.</li></ul><p>These are the same lights trusted by first responders and fleets across the country, now tuned to fit the needs of electric platforms.</p><h2>How to Choose the Right LED Lights for Your EV</h2><p>When you’re building an EV lighting package from this collection, start with these questions:</p><p><strong>1. What’s the EV’s role?</strong></p><ul><li>Patrol, response, or enforcement</li><li>Utility, public works, or service</li><li>Campus, security, or corporate fleet</li></ul><p><strong>2. Where do you need the most visibility?</strong></p><ul><li>Front and rear warning for highway EVs</li><li>Side/intersection warning for urban routes</li><li>Work-area lighting around the vehicle</li></ul><p><strong>3. Do you need permanent or reversible installs?</strong></p><ul><li>Leased EVs may favor dash lights, interior sticks, and non-drill mounts.</li><li>Owned fleet EVs can combine permanent mounts with hide-aways and rocker panels.</li></ul><p><strong>4. What colors and certifications are required?</strong></p><ul><li>Work with your agency or fleet manager to match color, flash patterns, and any SAE or NFPA requirements—then choose products in this collection that meet or exceed those standards.</li></ul><p>If you’re standardizing an all-electric fleet, you can use the same LED families across multiple vehicle models, simplifying training, maintenance, and spare parts.</p><h2>Why Buy LED EV Lights from Strobes N’ More?</h2><p>Strobes N’ More focuses exclusively on <a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">emergency and vehicle safety lighting</span></a>—this isn’t generic automotive styling. Here, you’ll find:</p><ul><li><strong>Curated, professional-grade brands</strong> like Strobes N’ More, Feniex, Federal Signal, SoundOff Signal, TowMate, Whelen, and more.</li><li><strong>Product pages with real specs and reviews</strong> so you can compare brightness, patterns, and mounting options with confidence.</li><li><strong>Support resources</strong> such as install guides, instructional videos, and service information to help ensure clean, reliable installations on modern EV platforms.</li></ul><p>Whether you’re wiring your first electric patrol SUV or outfitting an all-EV municipal fleet, this collection makes it straightforward to spec, buy, and deploy LED lights that are ready for the next generation of vehicles.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
    },
